.so fork.tmac
.SS SCREEN MANIPULATION
.PP
This series of functions make temporary adjustments to the screen
environment.
.PP
.cdef_voidfunc reset_screen
.sp -1
.IP
Simple function that erases the screen and sets the cursor to the
top left position.
.PP
.cdef_voidfunc set_cursor_position
.cdef_voidfunc get_cursor_position
.sp -1
.IP
Set the cursor position to paint specific areas of the screen.
On rare occasions, a program may also need to know where the cursor
is, too.
.PP
.cdef_voidfunc hide_cursor
.cdef_voidfunc show_cursor
.cdef_voidfunc normal_cursor
.sp -1
.IP
Hide the cursor to avoid the distraction of the cursor flashing
around when paintint the screen with text.
.B show_cursor
makes the cursor extra-bright if it is helpful to call attention to
the cursor.
Use
.B normal_cursor
to restore the cursor to the default brightness after having entered
either the
.BR hide_cursor " or " show_cursor
mode.















